{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "CloudAlbedoSensitivity",
        "description": "Twomey susceptibility and cloud albedo sensitivity to cloud droplet number concentration — Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Ch. 24 §24.8.2, Eqs. 24.40–24.41.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "radiative_forcing"
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "CloudAlbedoSensitivity": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition, Chapter 24, Section 24.8.2, Equations 24.40–24.41.",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb:src/aerosol_radiative_forcing.jl:254\nTwomey susceptibility: dR_c/dN = R_c*(1-R_c)/(3*N) (Eq. 24.40) and S = dR_c/d(ln N) = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 (Eq. 24.41). Both variables are closed-form algebraic functions of parameters only, so after MTK structural_simplify the system has zero ODE states and both dRc_dN and S are observed bindings. The inline-test runner samples them at their algebraic values at any requested time. S = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 does not depend on N; it reaches its maximum 1/12 ≈ 0.0833 at R_c = 0.5 and is symmetric: S(R_c) = S(1-R_c).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-8 / abs=1e-12): closed-form multiply-divide chains with no transcendental operations. rel=1e-8 captures float64 roundoff; abs=1e-12 floors the near-zero corners."
            },
            "variables": {
                "R_c": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.5,
                    "description": "Cloud albedo (dimensionless)"
                },
                "N": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 100000000.0,
                    "description": "Cloud droplet number concentration"
                },
                "dRc_dN": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "m^3",
                    "description": "Sensitivity of cloud albedo to CDNC, dR_c/dN = R_c*(1-R_c)/(3*N) (Eq. 24.40).",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "R_c",
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [-1, "R_c"]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [3, "N"]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "S": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Twomey susceptibility S = dR_c/d(ln N) = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 (Eq. 24.41). Maximum 1/12 ≈ 0.0833 at R_c = 0.5; independent of N.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "R_c",
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [-1, "R_c"]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            3
                        ]
                    }
                }
            },
            "equations": [],
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-8,
                "abs": 1e-12
            },
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_params_twomey_susceptibility",
                    "description": "Reproduces the default-parameter Twomey susceptibility from the upstream Aerosol.jl `Twomey Susceptibility - Eq. 24.40-24.41 Validation` testitem. At R_c=0.5, N=100 cm⁻³: S = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 = 1/12 ≈ 0.0833; dRc_dN = S/N = 1/(12×10⁸) ≈ 8.33×10⁻¹⁰ m³.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "N": 100000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.08333333333333333
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 8.333333333333334e-10
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 0.08333333333333333
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 8.333333333333334e-10
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "low_Rc_0p1_symmetry",
                    "description": "Symmetry check lower branch: R_c=0.1, N=100 cm⁻³. S = 0.1*0.9/3 = 0.03. Upstream asserts S(0.1) ≈ S(0.9) (symmetry of R_c*(1-R_c)/3 around R_c=0.5).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_c": 0.1,
                        "N": 100000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.030000000000000002
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 3.0000000000000005e-10
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "high_Rc_0p9_symmetry",
                    "description": "Symmetry check upper branch: R_c=0.9, N=100 cm⁻³. S = 0.9*0.1/3 ≈ 0.03. Confirms S(0.9) ≈ S(0.1) from upstream symmetry assertion.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_c": 0.9,
                        "N": 100000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.029999999999999995
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 2.9999999999999995e-10
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "mid_Rc_0p3_symmetry_pair",
                    "description": "Mid-sensitivity lower branch: R_c=0.3, N=100 cm⁻³. S = 0.3*0.7/3 = 0.07. Upstream asserts S(0.3) ≈ S(0.7) (symmetric pair).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_c": 0.3,
                        "N": 100000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.06999999999999999
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 7.0e-10
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "mid_Rc_0p7_symmetry_pair",
                    "description": "Mid-sensitivity upper branch: R_c=0.7, N=100 cm⁻³. S = 0.7*0.3/3 = 0.07. Confirms S(0.7) ≈ S(0.3) from upstream symmetry assertion.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_c": 0.7,
                        "N": 100000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.07
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 7.000000000000001e-10
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "N_sensitivity_half_N",
                    "description": "dRc_dN ∝ 1/N: halving N to 50 cm⁻³ doubles dRc_dN. S is N-independent and unchanged. Upstream asserts dRc_dN > 0 and max susceptibility at R_c=0.5.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "N": 50000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.6666666666666667e-9
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.08333333333333333
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "N_sensitivity_double_N",
                    "description": "dRc_dN ∝ 1/N: doubling N to 200 cm⁻³ halves dRc_dN. S is N-independent and unchanged.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "N": 200000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "dRc_dN",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 4.166666666666667e-10
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "S",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.08333333333333333
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "twomey_susceptibility_vs_Rc",
                    "description": "Twomey susceptibility S = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 as a function of cloud albedo R_c (Seinfeld & Pandis 2006, Eq. 24.41). The parabolic curve peaks at S = 1/12 ≈ 0.0833 at R_c = 0.5 and is symmetric: S(R_c) = S(1-R_c). Covers the full physical range R_c ∈ [0, 1].",
                    "parameters": {
                        "N": 100000000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "R_c",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.0,
                                    "stop": 1.0,
                                    "count": 50,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "S_vs_Rc",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Twomey susceptibility S plotted against cloud albedo R_c.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "R_c",
                                "label": "Cloud albedo R_c"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "S",
                                "label": "Twomey susceptibility S = dR_c/d(ln N)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "dRcdN_vs_Rc",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Cloud albedo sensitivity dR_c/dN plotted against cloud albedo R_c at N = 100 cm⁻³.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "R_c",
                                "label": "Cloud albedo R_c"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "dRc_dN",
                                "label": "dR_c/dN (m³)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dRcdN_vs_N",
                    "description": "Inverse-linear scaling of dR_c/dN with droplet number concentration N at fixed R_c = 0.5 (maximum susceptibility). dRc_dN = S/N, so a factor-10 increase in N reduces dRc_dN by a factor of 10. Covers the continental-to-pristine marine CDNC range.",
                    "parameters": {
                        "R_c": 0.5
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "N",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 10000000.0,
                                    "stop": 1000000000.0,
                                    "count": 40,
                                    "scale": "log"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dRcdN_vs_N",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "dR_c/dN as a function of CDNC N (log axis) at R_c = 0.5.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "N",
                                "label": "Cloud droplet number concentration N (m⁻³)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "dRc_dN",
                                "label": "dR_c/dN (m³)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "Rc_N_joint_sweep",
                    "description": "Joint sensitivity of dR_c/dN to cloud albedo R_c and droplet number concentration N. dRc_dN = R_c*(1-R_c)/(3*N) is separable: a parabola in R_c scaled by 1/N. The heatmap shows the combined peak-and-decay structure.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "R_c",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.05,
                                    "stop": 0.95,
                                    "count": 25,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "N",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 10000000.0,
                                    "stop": 1000000000.0,
                                    "count": 20,
                                    "scale": "log"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dRcdN_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "dR_c/dN(R_c, N) heatmap.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "R_c",
                                "label": "Cloud albedo R_c"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "N",
                                "label": "Cloud droplet number concentration N (m⁻³)"
                            },
                            "value": {
                                "variable": "dRc_dN",
                                "reduce": "final"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
